EBRD Donates 70 Million Euros More for Chernobyl Protection

-- B y   K a t e r y n a   C h o u r s i n a
-- 
2011-07-27T14:56:32Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-27/ebrd-donates-70-million-euros-more-for-chernobyl-protection.html
The European Bank for
Reconstruction and Development will donate another 70 million
euros ($101 million) to complete the protective shield at the
 Chernobyl  nuclear power station, the Ukrainian  Finance
Ministry  said.  London-based EBRD will provide the money in addition to
the 120 million euros announced at a donor conference in Kiev
on April 19, the Finance Ministry said on its  Website .  Ukraine has so far raised 740 million euros to complete a
new shelter over the No. 4 nuclear generator at Chernobyl,
which exploded 25 years ago, spewing radiation across  Europe .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Kateryna Choursina in Kiev at 
 kchoursina@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Carpenter at 
 ccarpenter2@bloomberg.net . 